    "notes": "Taiwan residential time-of-use tariff (Taipower), from the open rate tables on data.gov.tw (datasets 17052/17060). Published under the Open Government Data License, Taiwan (OGDL) — CC-BY-4.0-compatible; recorded as license:other, attributing Taipower / data.gov.tw. Summer = Jun–Sep carries higher rates via band.seasonRates. The block/tiered (non-ToU) residential tariff is not mapped (needs v1.1 tiers). Non-summer (Oct–May) has no peak band and uses different windows; v1 has one schedule, so the summer windows are canonical (peak 16:00–22:00, half-peak 09:00–16:00/22:00–24:00). Each band carries its summer/non-summer RATE via band.seasonRates — in winter the peak/half-peak windows are charged the non-summer half-peak rate, so window boundaries are approximate while the rates are the published values.",
